1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,503
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,586 --> 00:00:08,466
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,550 --> 00:00:10,427
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,510 --> 00:00:12,804
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,887 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:20,437
[Dmitri] <i>You gave birth</i>
<i>to a baby girl through C-section.</i>

7
00:00:20,520 --> 00:00:24,482
And years have passed,
but you never said anything.

8
00:00:24,566 --> 00:00:25,942
We're already searching for the child.

9
00:00:26,025 --> 00:00:27,402
My child is missing?

10
00:00:27,485 --> 00:00:29,904
You just gave her away
like a cat?! Is that it?!

11
00:00:29,988 --> 00:00:33,324
[in English] Class, let's all welcome
your new classmate.

12
00:00:33,408 --> 00:00:35,326
[Ibyang, in English]
<i>My name is Ivy Santos.</i>

13
00:00:35,410 --> 00:00:36,661
Just call me Ibyang.

14
00:00:36,745 --> 00:00:38,371
We just moved here.

15
00:00:38,455 --> 00:00:40,290
I came from somewhere far.

16
00:00:40,373 --> 00:00:42,083
What are your parents' names?

17
00:00:42,167 --> 00:00:44,461
- [girl] Where do they work?
- [Janine] <i>Hi, Ibyang!</i>

18
00:00:44,544 --> 00:00:45,754
[Janine] <i>Do you still remember me?</i>

19
00:00:45,837 --> 00:00:46,796
[thumps]

20
00:00:46,880 --> 00:00:47,881
[Ibyang] <i>Of course.</i>

21
00:00:47,964 --> 00:00:49,340
[Janine] <i>I'm Janine.</i>

22
00:00:49,424 --> 00:00:50,425
[Janine] How old are you?

23
00:00:50,508 --> 00:00:53,428
- Eight years old.
- <i>You should be in grade 2, Ibyang.</i>

24
00:00:53,511 --> 00:00:55,805
[Janine] <i>You must be dumb,</i>
<i>that's why they put you there.</i>

25
00:00:55,889 --> 00:00:58,224
[Red] <i>I'm finding a way to see the child.</i>

26
00:00:58,308 --> 00:00:59,309
- [thumps]
- [groans]

27
00:00:59,392 --> 00:01:00,602
[in English] This is all your fault!

28
00:01:00,685 --> 00:01:02,854
I know, I know!
That's why I'm trying to fix it, right?!

29
00:01:02,937 --> 00:01:04,606
[Atoy] Norma Cruz.

30
00:01:04,689 --> 00:01:06,024
She was the one who found her?

31
00:01:06,107 --> 00:01:09,277
She was the former directress
at Tahanan ng Bukas.

32
00:01:09,360 --> 00:01:10,528
She's a nun now.

33
00:01:10,612 --> 00:01:14,324
[Martina] Maybe you have information
you can give us about her.

34
00:01:14,407 --> 00:01:15,784
Ah, ma'am, that's difficult

35
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:18,286
because their official records
were already burned.

36
00:01:18,369 --> 00:01:21,414
Maybe this will motivate you
to help us find her?

37
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:25,835
[Mother Superior] Sister Norma is not
allowed to talk or entertain visitors,

38
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:28,755
not even relatives or police.

39
00:01:28,838 --> 00:01:30,006
[in English] She's very busy.

40
00:01:30,089 --> 00:01:32,801
[Gavin] <i>Is the mystery guy</i>
<i>from the island the father?</i>

41
00:01:32,884 --> 00:01:34,469
Does he know you have a child?

42
00:01:34,552 --> 00:01:37,096
Who knows? Maybe he even has your child.

43
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:40,558
[Audrey] <i>I just want to get</i>
<i>his personal number.</i>

44
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:42,519
[Mercado, in English]
<i>Classified information.</i>

45
00:01:42,602 --> 00:01:47,857
Uh, I'm sure your father already told you
we will no longer transact with you.

46
00:01:47,941 --> 00:01:48,817
‪PREVIOUSLY

47
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:50,360
[Mercado, in English] <i>Nothing personal.</i>

48
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:53,446
[music fades]

49
00:01:54,906 --> 00:01:56,199
[retches]

50
00:01:56,282 --> 00:01:58,284
[laughing]

51
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:00,328
What the…

52
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:03,915
[laughing]

53
00:02:03,998 --> 00:02:05,792
You laugh so loud!

54
00:02:06,751 --> 00:02:09,587
You're the one who put dirt
in my tumbler, right?

55
00:02:09,671 --> 00:02:11,339
So what? We're even.

56
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:15,135
My tumbler fell into the canal
because of you!

57
00:02:15,218 --> 00:02:16,511
What do you mean we're even?!

58
00:02:17,220 --> 00:02:19,430
I didn't feed you canal water!

59
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:22,100
And it was an accident!

60
00:02:23,059 --> 00:02:24,310
I already said sorry.

61
00:02:24,394 --> 00:02:26,563
So what? You'll tell on me?

62
00:02:27,188 --> 00:02:29,065
You don't even have parents.

63
00:02:29,149 --> 00:02:30,567
I do!

64
00:02:30,650 --> 00:02:32,777
Would I be alive if I didn't?

65
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:35,488
Maybe you're just adopted.

66
00:02:36,114 --> 00:02:37,949
Not true!

67
00:02:38,032 --> 00:02:39,075
[Janine] Ah, no.

68
00:02:39,742 --> 00:02:41,244
Oh, why is it that earlier in class,

69
00:02:41,327 --> 00:02:44,289
when the teacher asked
where your parents were,

70
00:02:44,372 --> 00:02:45,748
you didn't answer.

71
00:02:45,832 --> 00:02:49,085
Now, tell me their names.

72
00:02:50,670 --> 00:02:54,591
Oh, she's thinking of made-up names.

73
00:02:55,300 --> 00:02:56,426
So, you don't have any.

74
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,138
I do!

75
00:03:00,221 --> 00:03:03,266
Sis Ame, Sis Tonet, Sis Karla,

76
00:03:03,349 --> 00:03:06,686
Miss Cita, and Master Grumpy!

77
00:03:06,769 --> 00:03:08,605
Those aren't parents.

78
00:03:08,688 --> 00:03:11,357
Maybe you were just given away
when you were a baby.

79
00:03:11,441 --> 00:03:13,985
Maybe you were snotty,
so they didn't love you!

80
00:03:14,068 --> 00:03:16,279
[upbeat rock music playing]

81
00:03:20,950 --> 00:03:25,997
Thread, needle, scissors.

82
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:28,583
Thread, needle, scissors.

83
00:03:28,666 --> 00:03:29,876
Thread…

84
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:32,128
[suave theme music playing]

85
00:03:32,211 --> 00:03:34,047
[motorcycle revving]

86
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:35,006
[sewing machine whirring]

87
00:03:35,089 --> 00:03:36,925
[scratches]

88
00:03:37,008 --> 00:03:38,509
[snipping]

89
00:03:38,593 --> 00:03:39,469
[whirring]

90
00:03:40,511 --> 00:03:41,846
[sewing machine whirring]

91
00:03:42,722 --> 00:03:43,848
[gunshots blasting]

92
00:03:43,932 --> 00:03:45,808
[gunshots blasting]

93
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,518
[clacking]

94
00:03:47,602 --> 00:03:50,063
[snipping]

95
00:03:50,146 --> 00:03:53,024
[electronic blipping]

96
00:03:55,818 --> 00:03:57,612
[music fades]

97
00:03:58,488 --> 00:03:59,572
- Hey, Karla!
- Mmm?

98
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,741
Did you give my number to Jason?

99
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:03,201
He's texting me.

100
00:04:03,284 --> 00:04:04,327
No.

101
00:04:04,994 --> 00:04:06,913
Text him and ask how's Gavin.

102
00:04:06,996 --> 00:04:07,914
He hasn't reached out.

103
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,292
You do it.

104
00:04:12,794 --> 00:04:14,462
Why don't you text him?

105
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:17,632
[in English] You like the guy,
but you're shy.

106
00:04:17,715 --> 00:04:19,509
So, you're timid!

107
00:04:19,592 --> 00:04:21,511
Hey, I'm not timid!

108
00:04:21,594 --> 00:04:23,471
I'm not even planning to court him.

109
00:04:23,554 --> 00:04:26,307
Oh. Because you know,
it's modern times now.

110
00:04:26,391 --> 00:04:28,851
So, if the girl wants to pursue
the guy, she can!

111
00:04:28,935 --> 00:04:30,061
Hey!

112
00:04:30,144 --> 00:04:31,229
No, Brother Kurt!

113
00:04:31,312 --> 00:04:32,605
We're different here.

114
00:04:32,689 --> 00:04:36,693
Here, we want to be courted.

115
00:04:36,776 --> 00:04:39,028
- Right.
- [in English] We don't chase butterflies.

116
00:04:39,112 --> 00:04:43,241
[in English] We grow our garden and let
the butterflies come to us. Boom!

117
00:04:43,324 --> 00:04:44,409
- Like that.
- Okay, okay, okay.

118
00:04:44,492 --> 00:04:47,287
- That's right.
- I hope he courts you,

119
00:04:47,370 --> 00:04:49,747
and if not, it's his loss.

120
00:04:49,831 --> 00:04:51,165
[in English] True.

121
00:04:51,249 --> 00:04:54,460
[whimsical music playing]

122
00:04:54,544 --> 00:04:56,879
[sneaky music playing]

123
00:04:58,214 --> 00:05:00,174
[Karla] Ouch! What's that?!

124
00:05:00,258 --> 00:05:01,426
[Tonet] Mmm…

125
00:05:01,509 --> 00:05:03,219
- Karla.
- [thumps]

126
00:05:03,303 --> 00:05:04,595
- Oh. Sorry.
- Hey.

127
00:05:04,679 --> 00:05:06,222
[in English] Ah, sorry, sorry!

128
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:07,390
[in English] Gavin, sorry.

129
00:05:07,473 --> 00:05:08,933
It was Tonet-- Sis Tonet!

130
00:05:09,017 --> 00:05:10,685
- [in English] Sorry.
- It's okay.

131
00:05:12,645 --> 00:05:13,730
- [music fades]
- [Kurt] Wait.

132
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:17,025
- Is this the one you want to court?
- [quirky sting]

133
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:18,484
[Karla] Brother Kurt!

134
00:05:19,068 --> 00:05:19,986
[Gavin] What did he say?

135
00:05:20,570 --> 00:05:21,654
You want to court me?

136
00:05:22,238 --> 00:05:23,698
No!

137
00:05:23,781 --> 00:05:27,368
I want to lead you off track!
That's what he meant!

138
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:30,705
- Just joking!
- [sneaky music playing]

139
00:05:30,788 --> 00:05:33,916
I passed by the court,
but… you weren't there.

140
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,044
Oh! Come on!

141
00:05:36,127 --> 00:05:37,837
Let's play basketball with Billy!

142
00:05:37,920 --> 00:05:40,506
Ah, but our ball is gone.

143
00:05:41,007 --> 00:05:43,051
- Um…
- Is it okay if…

144
00:05:43,134 --> 00:05:44,594
it's just the two of us for now?

145
00:05:44,677 --> 00:05:46,387
[Tonet] That's the right thing
to do! [titters]

146
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:48,765
Right thing to do! That's okay!
Just the two of you, talk!

147
00:05:48,848 --> 00:05:50,183
[in English] Heart-to-heart,
heart-to-heart.

148
00:05:50,266 --> 00:05:52,393
There you go, so Karla can score
three points in your heart.

149
00:05:52,477 --> 00:05:53,936
- Tonet!
- [in English] Sorry.

150
00:05:54,020 --> 00:05:55,563
[Karla] Oh, um…

151
00:05:55,646 --> 00:05:57,398
Why? Why, Gavin?

152
00:05:57,482 --> 00:05:58,566
Is there a problem?

153
00:06:00,860 --> 00:06:02,695
[in English] God bless you, son.

154
00:06:02,779 --> 00:06:04,906
Come back another day.

155
00:06:04,989 --> 00:06:07,325
The food will be better.

156
00:06:07,408 --> 00:06:08,785
Ah, really? Okay, Sister.

157
00:06:12,455 --> 00:06:13,623
[woman] Thank you, Sister.

158
00:06:13,706 --> 00:06:15,124
Thank you.

159
00:06:16,584 --> 00:06:19,629
[nun 1] Sister, there's no more food.
Thank you very much.

160
00:06:19,712 --> 00:06:21,464
- We'll clean up now.
- [nun 2] Is that so?

161
00:06:21,547 --> 00:06:22,757
Okay.

162
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:25,176
[dramatic stinging]

163
00:06:25,259 --> 00:06:26,761
- Ah, Sister, just a picture.
- [nun mutters]

164
00:06:26,844 --> 00:06:29,138
- Yes, go ahead.
- I'll just take a picture.

165
00:06:29,222 --> 00:06:30,181
- [camera shutter snaps]
- There.

166
00:06:30,264 --> 00:06:32,183
Just for remembrance.

167
00:06:32,266 --> 00:06:33,476
[tense music playing]

168
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:34,644
[camera shutter snaps]

169
00:06:41,275 --> 00:06:42,110
[camera shutter snaps]

170
00:06:47,073 --> 00:06:47,949
[phone blips]

171
00:06:49,617 --> 00:06:50,451
‪[music concludes]

172
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,371
- Ma'am, I'll just step outside.
- [Audrey sighs]

173
00:06:53,454 --> 00:06:55,039
My child is out there.

174
00:06:55,123 --> 00:06:57,708
I'll hand something over
and give instructions.

175
00:06:57,792 --> 00:07:00,253
Um, just let her in, miss.

176
00:07:00,336 --> 00:07:02,421
So I can meet her too.

177
00:07:03,089 --> 00:07:05,383
- All right, ma'am.
- [Audrey] Okay.

178
00:07:11,806 --> 00:07:15,226
[pensive music playing]

179
00:07:15,309 --> 00:07:17,145
Ma'am, this is my child.

180
00:07:18,479 --> 00:07:19,730
Hi.

181
00:07:22,692 --> 00:07:24,861
Hello, ma'am. Sorry.

182
00:07:24,944 --> 00:07:26,446
Your baby?

183
00:07:26,529 --> 00:07:27,530
Yes.

184
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:30,241
[chuckles softly]

185
00:07:32,952 --> 00:07:34,203
Hi.

186
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:36,539
[chuckles softly]

187
00:07:38,040 --> 00:07:40,001
- Is it okay?
- [nurse] Go ahead, ma'am!

188
00:07:40,084 --> 00:07:42,712
You can hold her. You can carry her.

189
00:07:44,714 --> 00:07:45,548
‪[Audrey sighs]

190
00:07:48,593 --> 00:07:52,138
Is it hard to care for a baby?

191
00:07:52,221 --> 00:07:54,182
It's not only hard, ma'am,
but expensive too.

192
00:07:54,265 --> 00:07:56,309
That's why Mama helps financially.

193
00:07:57,059 --> 00:07:58,811
[nurse] Go ahead, ma'am.
You can carry her.

194
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:00,521
You can carry her, ma'am. Go ahead.

195
00:08:00,605 --> 00:08:02,482
No, no, I better not.

196
00:08:02,565 --> 00:08:04,192
I might hurt her.

197
00:08:11,616 --> 00:08:12,992
All right.

198
00:08:13,075 --> 00:08:15,161
[music swells]

199
00:08:15,244 --> 00:08:16,621
[gasps]

200
00:08:16,704 --> 00:08:18,498
[sentimental music playing]

201
00:08:18,581 --> 00:08:20,666
Gently…

202
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:24,003
[soft chuckle]

203
00:08:24,086 --> 00:08:28,132
Oh, ma'am. You hold her so naturally.

204
00:08:28,216 --> 00:08:30,092
Looks like you're ready to have a baby.

205
00:08:33,304 --> 00:08:34,347
[chuckles softly]

206
00:08:35,223 --> 00:08:36,933
You know…

207
00:08:38,476 --> 00:08:42,104
I'm a mother too, like you.

208
00:08:44,982 --> 00:08:47,527
I found out too late

209
00:08:48,194 --> 00:08:50,696
that I had a child eight years ago.

210
00:08:53,991 --> 00:08:55,785
Too bad, because…

211
00:08:57,912 --> 00:09:00,414
I never even knew her.

212
00:09:05,753 --> 00:09:09,507
I carried her for nine months…

213
00:09:11,842 --> 00:09:14,428
but I never saw her.

214
00:09:14,512 --> 00:09:17,348
[somber music playing]

215
00:09:17,431 --> 00:09:18,724
Now…

216
00:09:20,017 --> 00:09:21,185
she's gone.

217
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:24,522
[melancholic music playing]

218
00:09:25,189 --> 00:09:27,149
I never held her like this.

219
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:33,447
They took my child.

220
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:35,825
[dramatic sting]

221
00:09:35,908 --> 00:09:38,411
They just took her,
and I couldn't do anything.

222
00:09:48,045 --> 00:09:49,672
[sobbing]

223
00:09:51,591 --> 00:09:55,845
[delightful sigh]

224
00:10:00,558 --> 00:10:02,059
[sobs]

225
00:10:05,771 --> 00:10:06,689
[in English] Sorry.

226
00:10:08,024 --> 00:10:09,108
Thank you.

227
00:10:09,900 --> 00:10:11,360
[sobs]

228
00:10:13,529 --> 00:10:15,114
[Audrey, in English] Bye, baby.

229
00:10:15,197 --> 00:10:17,783
[soft chuckle]

230
00:10:22,747 --> 00:10:24,332
[Audrey] Thank you.

231
00:10:24,415 --> 00:10:26,584
[inhales]

232
00:10:31,672 --> 00:10:32,798
[Tonet] Twenty-eight, Miss Cita.

233
00:10:32,882 --> 00:10:33,966
[Cita, in English] Twenty-eight.

234
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:35,509
- [music fades]
- [Cita] Okay.

235
00:10:36,886 --> 00:10:38,137
[Tonet] Ah, thank you.

236
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,432
[Ame] Come on, let's go inside.
Let's go inside, let's go.

237
00:10:41,515 --> 00:10:42,725
- [Ame] We're going inside, come on.
- [Ibyang] Come on.

238
00:10:42,808 --> 00:10:43,893
[Ame] Here we go. Let's go.

239
00:10:45,936 --> 00:10:47,355
[Cita] Hey, Ibyang!

240
00:10:47,438 --> 00:10:48,898
Oh, bless.

241
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:51,108
How was your first day?

242
00:10:51,609 --> 00:10:52,902
[Atoy] So? How was it?

243
00:10:52,985 --> 00:10:54,195
How was your first day?

244
00:10:54,862 --> 00:10:56,405
[pensive music playing]

245
00:10:56,489 --> 00:10:57,823
[Atoy] Why, Ibyang?

246
00:10:57,907 --> 00:10:59,075
Is there a problem?

247
00:11:00,451 --> 00:11:02,411
Ah, nothing.

248
00:11:03,454 --> 00:11:05,706
The kids were kind.

249
00:11:05,790 --> 00:11:07,208
- Those aren't parents.
- [dramatic sting]

250
00:11:07,291 --> 00:11:09,710
- Maybe you were just given away as a baby.
- [dramatic sting]

251
00:11:09,794 --> 00:11:12,463
Maybe you were snotty,
so they didn't love you!

252
00:11:12,546 --> 00:11:15,466
They even treated me to a chocolate drink.

253
00:11:15,549 --> 00:11:16,967
[dramatic sting]

254
00:11:17,051 --> 00:11:18,010
[retches, spits]

255
00:11:18,094 --> 00:11:19,845
- [laughing]
- [dramatic sting]

256
00:11:19,929 --> 00:11:22,515
- Son of a thread!
- [laughing]

257
00:11:22,598 --> 00:11:23,432
‪[dramatic sting]

258
00:11:26,018 --> 00:11:27,228
You laugh so loud!

259
00:11:27,311 --> 00:11:30,064
[Ibyang] You're the one
who put dirt in my tumbler, right?

260
00:11:30,147 --> 00:11:31,732
Did you eat your lunch?

261
00:11:31,816 --> 00:11:33,109
Yes.

262
00:11:33,192 --> 00:11:34,360
It was delicious.

263
00:11:34,443 --> 00:11:36,529
[dramatic sting]

264
00:11:38,531 --> 00:11:40,366
- [Cita] Ah!
- Good. There you go.

265
00:11:40,449 --> 00:11:41,575
[in English] Very good.

266
00:11:41,659 --> 00:11:42,701
[Tonet] There you go.

267
00:11:42,785 --> 00:11:44,620
Oh, maybe you're still hungry!

268
00:11:44,703 --> 00:11:45,871
- Snack?
- Come on, let's eat snacks.

269
00:11:45,955 --> 00:11:47,331
- Maybe you're hungry.
- Come on, come on.

270
00:11:47,415 --> 00:11:49,792
- Let's eat first.
- [Ibyang] Let's eat snacks!

271
00:11:52,962 --> 00:11:54,505
[music fades]

272
00:11:54,588 --> 00:11:56,298
Oh, Atoy,

273
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:57,383
what's that for?

274
00:11:58,175 --> 00:11:59,552
[snipping]

275
00:11:59,635 --> 00:12:00,636
Nothing.

276
00:12:01,262 --> 00:12:05,599
[mysterious music playing]

277
00:12:05,683 --> 00:12:07,685
I'll enter a convent.

278
00:12:07,768 --> 00:12:09,520
- Hey.
- [Atoy] There.

279
00:12:10,312 --> 00:12:12,523
So I can talk to Sister Norma.

280
00:12:13,065 --> 00:12:17,653
She's the only one who knows
where Ibyang really came from.

281
00:12:19,280 --> 00:12:21,115
Be careful.

282
00:12:21,699 --> 00:12:23,367
They're close to God.

283
00:12:23,451 --> 00:12:25,327
I'm sure I'll come out alive.

284
00:12:26,579 --> 00:12:29,582
You never know,
maybe a snake will slither in.

285
00:12:30,249 --> 00:12:34,128
[suspicious music playing]

286
00:12:36,338 --> 00:12:38,299
I feel bad for your aunt.

287
00:12:38,382 --> 00:12:42,011
She found out her child is missing,
while she was experiencing appendicitis.

288
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:48,559
[Gavin] I don't even know
which hurts more.

289
00:12:49,602 --> 00:12:52,021
Being hurt by your own body

290
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:53,439
or by your own family.

291
00:12:53,522 --> 00:12:55,191
[ball thuds]

292
00:13:02,907 --> 00:13:04,241
How's your aunt now?

293
00:13:04,325 --> 00:13:05,618
[in English] She's not okay.

294
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:08,287
[in English] I feel bad for her.

295
00:13:08,370 --> 00:13:10,956
Oh, not just because of the betrayal.

296
00:13:11,040 --> 00:13:13,459
But because the time they could spend
together as mother and child was wasted.

297
00:13:13,542 --> 00:13:16,337
They should be bonding now,
loving each other.

298
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,671
[ball thuds]

299
00:13:24,887 --> 00:13:26,013
[in English] True.

300
00:13:28,766 --> 00:13:31,143
Time should never be wasted on anything.

301
00:13:31,227 --> 00:13:34,396
Especially the time
to be true to yourself.

302
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,398
[gentle music playing]

303
00:13:40,152 --> 00:13:42,196
[ball thudding]

304
00:13:43,614 --> 00:13:44,782
[in English] What do you mean?

305
00:13:45,950 --> 00:13:48,994
When you need to say something
from the heart,

306
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:50,704
say it.

307
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:53,707
It's never wrong
if it comes from the heart, right?

308
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:56,502
So, no time or chances are wasted.

309
00:13:58,879 --> 00:14:04,343
[sentimental music playing]

310
00:14:04,927 --> 00:14:06,428
Why are you looking at me like that?

311
00:14:06,512 --> 00:14:08,013
[in English] Nothing.

312
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:09,473
[in English] You're right, Karla.

313
00:14:09,557 --> 00:14:11,684
[in English] You make so much sense.

314
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,394
I'm glad I talked to you today.

315
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:14,728
[ball thuds]

316
00:14:22,945 --> 00:14:24,196
[music fades]

317
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:25,489
[gun cocks]

318
00:14:25,573 --> 00:14:30,077
So, you never saw the tailor's child
again after you beat him up?

319
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,787
Your boys, huh?

320
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:32,705
What was his name?

321
00:14:33,330 --> 00:14:34,707
Atoy!

322
00:14:34,790 --> 00:14:36,959
He's no longer there.

323
00:14:37,042 --> 00:14:38,460
If i see that fool,

324
00:14:38,544 --> 00:14:40,087
- it's a head shot from me!
- [gun cocks]

325
00:14:40,170 --> 00:14:41,630
- [gun's trigger clicks]
- [grunts]

326
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:45,926
- [suspicious music playing]
- [Martina sighs]

327
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:50,222
The social worker just told me
Norma Cruz is housed in a convent.

328
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:54,393
What's she doing there?

329
00:14:54,476 --> 00:14:56,478
She's a nun now.

330
00:14:57,271 --> 00:14:59,273
[sighs, in English]
We can talk to her tomorrow.

331
00:15:00,024 --> 00:15:02,526
[in English] She doesn't know my name,
but I'm sure she'll remember my face.

332
00:15:06,739 --> 00:15:08,198
Come with me.

333
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:09,241
[in English] Yes, Boss.

334
00:15:10,451 --> 00:15:12,244
[in English] Uh… Hon, please.

335
00:15:12,328 --> 00:15:13,579
[in English] No guns tomorrow.

336
00:15:13,662 --> 00:15:15,372
You have to look like
you're meeting the pope.

337
00:15:29,929 --> 00:15:33,807
[bell tolling]

338
00:15:34,808 --> 00:15:39,980
[sacred music playing]

339
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:00,584
[in English] Sister!

340
00:16:01,293 --> 00:16:04,046
[sneaky music playing]

341
00:16:04,129 --> 00:16:05,381
[woman] Good morning, Sister!

342
00:16:05,464 --> 00:16:07,091
Child, bless.

343
00:16:10,219 --> 00:16:15,808
Grandma, why do Sister's hands
look like a man's hands?

344
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:18,102
Oh, goodness, child!

345
00:16:18,185 --> 00:16:20,145
She blessed you!

346
00:16:20,229 --> 00:16:22,648
And you insult Sister?

347
00:16:22,731 --> 00:16:24,358
[scoffs] Let's go!

348
00:16:24,441 --> 00:16:29,571
[soft rock music playing]

349
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:38,330
[in English] I-I-I'm sorry. What?

350
00:16:38,414 --> 00:16:41,834
Sister Norma is on a one-year
vow of silence?

351
00:16:41,917 --> 00:16:43,460
[in English] Yes.

352
00:16:43,544 --> 00:16:46,964
She cannot be spoken to
or visited by anyone

353
00:16:47,047 --> 00:16:48,507
because she will not speak.

354
00:16:49,758 --> 00:16:51,301
What kind of gimmick is that?

355
00:16:51,385 --> 00:16:53,554
[sinister music playing]

356
00:16:53,637 --> 00:16:55,139
[in English] Sorry, Sister Ludy.

357
00:16:55,222 --> 00:16:57,474
[in English] It's just that it's the first
time we've heard of such a thing.

358
00:16:57,558 --> 00:17:00,019
This is not a gimmick.

359
00:17:00,978 --> 00:17:03,272
[in English] Silence
is a form of worship.

360
00:17:03,355 --> 00:17:07,359
[in English] It is a way
of attentively listening to God's voice.

361
00:17:08,527 --> 00:17:10,529
[music fades]

362
00:17:12,948 --> 00:17:14,533
- Sister Norma, Sister Norma!
- [Mother Superior, in English] Excuse me?!

363
00:17:14,616 --> 00:17:16,118
- [Red, in English] Ah… Wait.
- Excuse me!

364
00:17:16,201 --> 00:17:19,997
Eight years ago, my wife
handed you a two-month-old baby.

365
00:17:20,080 --> 00:17:22,499
Her name is Martina. Martina Regalia.

366
00:17:22,583 --> 00:17:24,043
Do you remember?

367
00:17:24,126 --> 00:17:25,753
Sister, do you still remember me?

368
00:17:25,836 --> 00:17:27,337
We just want to find the child.

369
00:17:27,421 --> 00:17:29,798
We want to know who adopted her.

370
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:32,176
Please, don't disturb us!

371
00:17:32,259 --> 00:17:34,970
She has nothing to say
because she is not Sister Norma!

372
00:17:35,888 --> 00:17:36,847
Don't lie.

373
00:17:36,930 --> 00:17:38,515
I just want to talk to her, Sister.
What's the matter?

374
00:17:38,599 --> 00:17:40,976
Come, let's talk. Just for a moment. Come!

375
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:42,102
- This will just take a moment.
- [in English] Sir, please!

376
00:17:42,186 --> 00:17:43,270
- Let her go!
- [clamoring]

377
00:17:43,353 --> 00:17:44,354
[in English] You are harassing her!

378
00:17:44,438 --> 00:17:46,565
[Mother Superior] We already said
she's not Sister Norma!

379
00:17:46,648 --> 00:17:48,650
She is Sister Tessie!

380
00:17:48,734 --> 00:17:50,110
She is deaf-mute!

381
00:17:50,194 --> 00:17:52,738
And even if you were face-to-face
with Sister Norma,

382
00:17:52,821 --> 00:17:54,573
she could not entertain you!

383
00:17:55,449 --> 00:17:56,909
- What do you mean deaf-mute--
- Hon…

384
00:17:56,992 --> 00:17:58,786
[in English] I just realized
that it's not her.

385
00:17:58,869 --> 00:18:00,079
[in English] I-I'm sorry, it's not her.

386
00:18:00,996 --> 00:18:02,206
Really?

387
00:18:02,289 --> 00:18:04,666
[tense music playing]

388
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:07,169
Sister Rose, call the security guard.

389
00:18:07,252 --> 00:18:08,962
[stammers, in English] I'm so sorry.

390
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:10,506
[in English] It just got a little bit
out of hand.

391
00:18:10,589 --> 00:18:11,715
[in English] I'm sorry, Sister.

392
00:18:11,799 --> 00:18:13,926
- [Red sighs] Uh…
- [guard] Excuse me, sir.

393
00:18:14,009 --> 00:18:15,344
Let's go outside.

394
00:18:16,804 --> 00:18:19,181
- All right.
- [in English] Please, leave!

395
00:18:19,264 --> 00:18:20,808
[in English] Yes. Sorry.

396
00:18:27,981 --> 00:18:30,859
[music fades]

397
00:18:32,778 --> 00:18:38,075
- [indistinct chatter]
- [utensils clattering]

398
00:18:46,041 --> 00:18:48,961
[pensive music playing]

399
00:18:51,672 --> 00:18:52,673
[in English] Sister?

400
00:18:53,924 --> 00:18:55,509
Do you still have food?

401
00:18:55,592 --> 00:18:56,677
[sneaky music playing]

402
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:57,886
Hmm, Sister,

403
00:18:58,554 --> 00:18:59,680
maybe you have something kept aside?

404
00:19:00,389 --> 00:19:02,599
Ah, son, there are no more food packs.

405
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,560
- Come back another day.
- No more?!

406
00:19:05,185 --> 00:19:06,353
I'm hungry.

407
00:19:08,021 --> 00:19:09,356
Ah, let me help you!

408
00:19:12,943 --> 00:19:14,611
That nun is so cranky.

409
00:19:20,659 --> 00:19:21,952
[softly] This is a store.

410
00:19:23,495 --> 00:19:26,623
[pensive music playing]

411
00:19:33,922 --> 00:19:35,507
[music fades]

412
00:19:37,092 --> 00:19:40,429
[in English] That woman's name
is Martina Regalia.

413
00:19:41,263 --> 00:19:43,807
She supposedly left a child with you.

414
00:19:43,891 --> 00:19:45,809
Do you remember?

415
00:19:45,893 --> 00:19:47,311
[pensive music playing]

416
00:19:47,936 --> 00:19:50,564
Are they the parents
of the child they're looking for?

417
00:19:55,944 --> 00:19:57,279
[paper rustling]

418
00:19:58,739 --> 00:20:02,993
[suspicious music playing]

419
00:20:10,667 --> 00:20:14,254
DO YOU HAVE MARTINA'S CONTACT NUMBER?

420
00:20:14,338 --> 00:20:17,549
MAYBE THEY'RE LOOKING FOR THE CHILD
TO RETURN HER TO THE REAL PARENTS

421
00:20:17,633 --> 00:20:18,884
I CAN HELP HER

422
00:20:21,762 --> 00:20:23,889
I don't have their contact number,

423
00:20:23,972 --> 00:20:26,433
and I have no intention of finding them.

424
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,978
If their purpose is to return
the child to her real parents,

425
00:20:30,062 --> 00:20:33,065
why don't the parents
talk to you themselves?

426
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:38,153
Why are they so aggressive
about wanting to know where the child is?

427
00:20:40,280 --> 00:20:42,741
[in English] I just have
a bad feeling about them.

428
00:20:43,784 --> 00:20:47,454
I would not trust them
with the child they are looking for.

429
00:20:48,372 --> 00:20:52,751
[music intensifies]

430
00:20:55,587 --> 00:20:58,882
[nun 1] Why are they forcing Sister Norma
to speak?

431
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:01,385
[nun 2] Sister Norma was once
the head of the orphanage,

432
00:21:01,468 --> 00:21:04,972
and they say a child was given to her.

433
00:21:05,055 --> 00:21:06,848
Sister Ludy got angry.

434
00:21:06,932 --> 00:21:08,642
So, she sent them away.

435
00:21:08,725 --> 00:21:10,269
[nun 1] Who were they?

436
00:21:11,353 --> 00:21:12,646
[nun 2] They said a married couple.

437
00:21:12,729 --> 00:21:15,274
But I didn't get their names.

438
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:17,943
[nun 1] But why would they look for her
if they already gave her away?

439
00:21:18,026 --> 00:21:22,072
[suspicious music playing]

440
00:21:30,956 --> 00:21:32,791
[music fades]

441
00:21:36,878 --> 00:21:37,796
[Janine] Ibyang!

442
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,215
I already saw your parents.

443
00:21:40,966 --> 00:21:42,926
You don't believe me?

444
00:21:44,553 --> 00:21:46,722
This is your mother.

445
00:21:46,805 --> 00:21:47,764
[pensive music playing]

446
00:21:47,848 --> 00:21:49,224
[Janine snickers]

447
00:21:49,308 --> 00:21:52,102
And this is your father.

448
00:21:52,811 --> 00:21:53,979
When you put them together,

449
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:55,856
ta-da!

450
00:21:56,565 --> 00:21:57,524
Color black.

451
00:21:58,275 --> 00:21:59,401
That's you, Ibyang.

452
00:22:00,193 --> 00:22:01,611
Because you're nothing.

453
00:22:02,279 --> 00:22:03,530
Ibyang, nothing!

454
00:22:03,613 --> 00:22:05,574
No parents!

455
00:22:05,657 --> 00:22:07,159
[all] Ibyang, nothing!

456
00:22:07,242 --> 00:22:09,328
No parents!

457
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:10,912
Ibyang, nothing!

458
00:22:10,996 --> 00:22:12,664
No parents!

459
00:22:12,748 --> 00:22:13,874
Ibyang, nothing!

460
00:22:13,957 --> 00:22:15,584
No parents!

461
00:22:15,667 --> 00:22:17,669
Ibyang, nothing!

462
00:22:17,753 --> 00:22:18,795
No parents!

463
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:20,255
Ibyang, nothing!

464
00:22:20,339 --> 00:22:22,424
No parents!

465
00:22:22,507 --> 00:22:25,052
Ibyang, nothing! No parents!

466
00:22:26,344 --> 00:22:27,763
[music fades]

467
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:30,015
[utensils clattering]

468
00:22:30,098 --> 00:22:34,019
Ah, Sister, Sister Norma's quarters
are still being prepared.

469
00:22:34,102 --> 00:22:35,562
Just bring that to the Rose Garden.

470
00:22:35,645 --> 00:22:37,189
She's there.

471
00:22:37,272 --> 00:22:40,942
[suspicious music playing]

472
00:22:42,736 --> 00:22:44,029
[door hinge squeaks]

473
00:22:50,035 --> 00:22:51,119
[music fades]

474
00:22:51,203 --> 00:22:52,746
[Sister Ludy] Sister…

475
00:22:52,829 --> 00:22:55,582
Why are you the one
bringing food to Sister Norma?

476
00:22:55,665 --> 00:22:58,001
[rousing music playing]

477
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:01,546
[electronic blipping]

478
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:05,592
[tense music playing]

479
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:10,722
Sister Norma, don't be afraid of me.

480
00:23:10,806 --> 00:23:12,599
[Atoy] <i>I'm Atoy, I just…</i>

481
00:23:12,682 --> 00:23:14,392
<i>I just need to know something from you.</i>

482
00:23:14,476 --> 00:23:16,728
[Red] <i>That vow of silence is nonsense.</i>

483
00:23:16,812 --> 00:23:19,022
Look, if I point a gun at her,
she'll do a monologue.

484
00:23:19,106 --> 00:23:20,398
Why didn't we just do that?!

485
00:23:20,482 --> 00:23:21,900
Tonight, let's go back here.

486
00:23:21,983 --> 00:23:23,360
[Red] <i>Let's break in.</i>

487
00:23:23,443 --> 00:23:24,861
[gun cocks]

488
00:23:24,945 --> 00:23:27,697
Nothing will happen unless
you tell me where Sister Norma is.

489
00:23:28,406 --> 00:23:29,866
[Sister Ludy] Sister Norma!

490
00:23:29,950 --> 00:23:31,159
‪UP NEXT

491
00:23:31,243 --> 00:23:32,410
[Red] Stop!

492
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,746
- [gunshots]
- [grunting]

493
00:23:35,956 --> 00:23:37,249
[Atoy] Sister, run!

494
00:23:37,332 --> 00:23:39,084
- [grunting]
- [gunshots]

495
00:23:39,167 --> 00:23:41,211
‪♪ <i>‪Holding the scissors</i>‪ ♪

496
00:23:41,294 --> 00:23:44,172
‪♪ <i>‪One cut, and it's settled</i>‪ ♪

497
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:46,591
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
